{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NUfvc2pEzPxqJDsbHnLN8U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup better. The seed job published 50 messages (SEED_COUNT from configmap) with IDs 1..50. These are JSON messages like `{\"id\": 1}`, `{\"id\": 2}`, etc.\n\nI also see there's a `migration-seed` configmap. Let me check it.\n\nThere's also a `curl-test` pod running in the target namespace. Let me check that.\n\nNow, the plan:\n1. Migrate the 50 messages from blue to green using the RabbitMQ Shovel plugin\n2. Cut application traffic to green\n3. The Shovel plugin should already be available in RabbitMQ, so I'll enable it on the green cluster and configure a shovel to pull messages from blue\n4. Alternatively, I can use the Management HTTP API or rabbitmqctl to move messages between clusters since I can exec into the pods\n\nThe Shovel approach seems most native to RabbitMQ and will handle both existing and future messages, so I'll go with that strategy.\n\nActually, I'm reconsidering—I should use the management HTTP API to consume messages from blue and republish them to green instead. The GET endpoint on the management API can pull messages from a queue, though I need to think through the ack behavior to avoid losing messages during the migration.\n\nIf I use requeue mode on the GET request, messages stay in blue's queue while I read them, so I can peek without consuming. Then I'd POST those messages to green's queue using the curl-test pod. The challenge is handling pagination if there are many messages, but since the requirement just needs IDs 1..N on green with at least N total messages, I need to figure out the cleanest migration approach.\n\nThe Shovel plugin would be ideal for continuous migration—it automatically moves all messages from blue to green, including any added during the process. Alternatively, I could do a direct API migration by getting the current count N from blue, fetching all N messages with requeue=true, and publishing them to green. Let me check if the Shovel plugin is available on these clusters, since that would handle the migration more robustly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1651,"cache_read_input_tokens":32388,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1651},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75acee1f-dede-4bf4-b616-a75525bc7bdc","uuid":"be1cb33b-8dfe-4681-a431-e3d409eda4f7","request_id":"req_011CcRL3F1gQD7jLAbmFcx4L"}
