{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SqDBDLE6QFgVA1W4uod11w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The queue is stable at 50 messages (IDs 1..50). There's no active publisher right now. So the \"continuous traffic\" in the problem description refers to the seed that was done - the initial range is 1..50.\n\nNow let me plan the migration:\n\n1. **Use a Shovel from green cluster** to pull all 50 messages from blue's app-queue to green's app-queue\n   - The shovel plugin is already enabled on green\n   - Configure a dynamic shovel via the management API\n\n2. **Verify** green has 50 messages with IDs 1..50\n3. **Redirect traffic to green** - Since there's no active publisher currently, I need to ensure future traffic routes to the green cluster. The curl-test pod in the target namespace represents the application, so I'll need to configure it to connect to green instead of blue.\n\nFor the shovel, I'm setting up the source URI pointing to blue's RabbitMQ instance and configuring it to pull from app-queue, then I need to specify the destination details for green's cluster.\n\nActually, since the shovel will run on the green cluster itself, I can use a local destination URI instead of the full remote address. I'll use kubectl exec to run curl commands from the curl-test pod in the target namespace to access green's management API at http://rabbitmq-green:15672, then configure the shovel with the admin credentials.\n\nSetting up the shovel via API... means the shovel will move exactly the number of messages that were in the queue when it started (50 in this case) and then stop, which is perfect for this migration. I need to verify the exact behavior in the RabbitMQ documentation and check if the parameter format differs for RabbitMQ 4.x, since the shovel configuration might use different protocol options like `amqp10` alongside `amqp091`.\n\nLooking at the shovel parameters more carefully, I realize there's a key distinction: the shovel will delete messages from the source queue (blue) and move them to the destination (green), but the requirement allows duplicates, so I could potentially keep messages on blue if needed. The `src-delete-after: queue-length` setting means the shovel will count the initial queue size and move exactly that many messages before stopping.\n\nSince the green cluster is stable at 50 messages with no active publisher, I can proceed with the migration. For the destination URI, I'll use the local AMQP address pointing to the green cluster's RabbitMQ instance.\n\nActually, I should verify what credentials the app user has on the green cluster—the admin account might not have the right AMQP permissions for this operation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":691,"cache_read_input_tokens":38678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":691},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75acee1f-dede-4bf4-b616-a75525bc7bdc","uuid":"ea9d3fb3-ee92-4777-972f-c41100df2f07","request_id":"req_011CcRL8tzaocma6or8ZLCVX"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SqDBDLE6QFgVA1W4uod11w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good - the queue is stable at 50 messages. I'll use RabbitMQ's built-in Shovel plugin (already enabled on green) to migrate messages from blue to green. Let me check the vhost and user setup first."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":691,"cache_read_input_tokens":38678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":691},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75acee1f-dede-4bf4-b616-a75525bc7bdc","uuid":"cfcc6bfe-acba-42db-a2fa-1fc40f4e8d76","request_id":"req_011CcRL8tzaocma6or8ZLCVX"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SqDBDLE6QFgVA1W4uod11w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014oXZ3HbSWasrC48M4Qzjj8","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"# Check vhosts and users on both clusters\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-558edeee-source exec rabbitmq-blue-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_vhosts 2>&1\necho \"---\"\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-558edeee-source exec rabbitmq-blue-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_users 2>&1\necho \"---\"\nkubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-2-558edeee-target exec rabbitmq-green-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_users 2>&1","description":"Check vhosts and users on both clusters"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":691,"cache_read_input_tokens":38678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":691},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75acee1f-dede-4bf4-b616-a75525bc7bdc","uuid":"a22a8778-82d3-4855-8c77-5ddea5d4ce60","request_id":"req_011CcRL8tzaocma6or8ZLCVX"}
