{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V3ckL5moSUCDsTDVVL1kvj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can reach the blue management API from the green namespace. Now I need to set up the shovel.\n\nFor the shovel, I'll configure it on the green cluster via the management API. The shovel will:\n1. Source: blue's app-queue in /app vhost\n2. Destination: green's app-queue in /app vhost\n3. `src-delete-after: queue-length` - moves exactly the current number of messages (50) then stops\n\nWait, but I need to think about this more carefully. In RabbitMQ 4.x, the shovel parameters changed slightly from 3.x. Let me think about the right configuration.\nActually, looking at the 4.x API, I need to use the parameters endpoint to configure the shovel with the right protocol and URI settings. For the destination, since the shovel runs on green, I can connect locally to green's AMQP broker using localhost with the app credentials and /app vhost. Finishing the shovel configuration with the destination pointing to localhost and setting it to delete messages after moving them based on the current queue length. I'll use the PUT endpoint to create this shovel in the app vhost, then execute it from the curl-test pod. Since there's no active publisher right now, the 50 messages in the queue should move cleanly without race conditions.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":254,"cache_read_input_tokens":41913,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":254},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75acee1f-dede-4bf4-b616-a75525bc7bdc","uuid":"4172356b-dbc0-48a2-84e6-fd0c5079cde0","request_id":"req_011CcRLCzKBBQuaf2JfZBhbW"}
