{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019oaiFmMS1ftufPefAJ7Nbb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The shovel completed successfully:\n- Blue queue: 0 messages (all migrated)\n- Green queue: 50 messages (all received)\n- Shovel status: `[]` (empty, meaning the shovel has completed and been removed since `src-delete-after: queue-length`)\n\nNow I need to verify the green queue has the correct messages (IDs 1..50 without gaps), and also \"cut application traffic to green\".\n\nLet me verify the messages first by peeking at a few using the management API. Then I'll check what \"cut application traffic to green\" means in this context.\nI can verify the messages are correct by using the management API to peek at messages on green and check for IDs 1 through 50 without gaps. For \"cutting traffic to green\", since there's no active publisher currently running in the source namespace, I need to ensure any future publishers use the green cluster and the application connects to green. The curl-test pod is already in the target namespace, so the migration appears complete, but let me re-read the requirements to make sure I'm not missing anything.\n\nThe requirements specify that green should contain the initial seed range (IDs 1 through N) with no gaps, at least N messages are available on green, and the blue-to-green migration is complete enough for consumers to proceed. With N=50, I need to verify there are no gaps in the message IDs. I'll use the management API's peek endpoint to sample the messages and check their IDs, since each message is a JSON object with an \"id\" field from the seed job.\n\nSince the shovel preserved message content while moving them from blue to green, and the seed job published them sequentially (1, 2, 3... 50), they should maintain that order in green's queue. Let me spot-check a few messages to confirm.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_detai